name: The old 24th St Pedestrian Bridge in Minneapolis
description: A bridge over i-35W that offered a beautiful vantage point for one pretty city, and served as a favorite spot for local photographers to capture Minneapolis. This was shot in the spring of 2018, just before the bridge was torn down as part of a 35W/94 reconstruction project. This photo was also featured in the grand opening of the new iteration of the bridge that opened in August 2021, on display along the bridge's new fence, as part of MN-DOT's 'Bridge Fest.'
